trend_summary: Built-up footprint grows moderately: quarry expands, a central institutional/industrial campus adds blocks and parking, and new suburban subdivisions fill gaps east of the highway. Road network intensifies with extra lanes and ramps. Resulting development trims forest edges and converts some western farmland, but overall green space still dominates.
notable_changes: North-west quarry enlarges and deepens, replacing adjacent fields.
Central campus/industrial zone adds several large roofs and paved lots.
Multiple cul-de-sac housing clusters appear east of the main freeway.
Primary highway widened; new interchange or slip roads constructed.
Progressive loss of forest and farmland, especially along transport corridors.
